OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780851961
OL,3,CVillage hit by 'big thud' earthquake
OL,4,Cfor second time in three weeks
OL,6,F"Additional Information: The quake was
OL,7,Ffelt around the Morecambe bay area.
OL,8,FReports described 'a big thud', 'like
OL,9,Fa distant explosion', and 'a burst of
OL,10,Fnoise'".
OL,12,FAccording to the BGS, the driving
OL,13,Fforces for earthquake activity in the
OL,14,FUK are unclear.
OL,16,FThey include regional compression
OL,17,Fcaused by motion of the Earth's
OL,18,Ftectonic plates and uplift resulting
OL,19,Ffrom the melting of the ice sheets
OL,20,Fthat covered many parts of Britain
OL,21,Fthousands of years ago.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780851961
OL,3,CVillage hit by 'big thud' earthquake
OL,4,Cfor second time in three weeks
OL,6,FEach year, between 200 and 300
OL,7,Fearthquakes are detected and located
OL,8,Fin the UK. Between 20 to 30
OL,9,Fearthquakes are felt by people each
OL,10,Fyear, and a few hundred smaller ones
OL,11,Fare only recorded by sensitive
OL,12,Finstruments.
OL,14,FMost of these are very small and cause
OL,15,Fno damage. However, some British
OL,16,Fearthquakes have caused considerable
OL,17,Fdamage, although nothing like the
OL,18,Fdevastation caused by large
OL,19,Fearthquakes in other parts of the
OL,20,Fworld.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
